doc:
Sealed Game module for Love Letter with Seal Integration
 Main game logic with encrypted cards and commitment verification

play_turn.doc: Play a turn - player reveals card value with proof

execute_guard.doc: Guard (1): Set pending response for target to reveal

execute_priest.doc: Priest (2): Grant temporary access to view target's card

execute_baron.doc: Baron (3): Set pending response for comparison

hand_contains_value.doc: Check if player's hand contains a specific card value

seal_approve_card.doc: Entry function for Seal servers to verify card access

Player.doc: Player state in a game (card indices only, not values!)

hand.doc: Card indices in hand (NOT card values - values are encrypted)

discarded.doc: Revealed discarded cards (values visible after discard)

data.doc: Additional data (e.g., guess for Guard, attacker's card for Baron)

SealedGameRoom.doc: Game room with Seal integration - shared object

deck_values.doc: Original deck values (set at round start, used for commitment)

deck_secrets.doc: Secrets for each card (for commitment verification)

commitments.doc: Commitments for each card: hash(value || secret)

deck_indices.doc: Remaining card indices in deck (not dealt yet)

RoomRegistry.doc: Registry to track all active rooms
